tourBios.carHigh:
2014: Finished T118 at Web.com Tour Q-School Finals in December.

Played the Dakotas Tour in 2011-2014 and the Gateway Tour in 2013-14. Lone Web.com Tour start prior to 2015 came at the Preferred Health Systems Wichita Open in 2012 (missed cut).
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Was a two-time Academic All-American and won two tournaments, the Kansas Invitational and the Bill Ross Intercollegiate, while playing at the University of Kansas...Was medalist at the 2006 South Dakota High School state championship.
tourBios.personal: Plays a lot of golf with former Chicago Bears middle linebacker Brian Urlacher in Phoenix...Would like to trade places with Dallas Mavericks' owner Mark Cuban for a day...Has made 10 aces in his life...Carries the state quarters of Nebraska and Wyoming in his bag for good luck...Favorite quote is "Anything less than your best is a sacrifice to the gift" from long-distance runner Steve Prefontaine...First tee intro song would be "Wherever I May Roam" by Metallica...If not a pro golfer, would be a meteorologist or park ranger...Favorite teams are Denver Broncos and Phoenix Suns...Favorite entertainers are Neil Young and Red Hot Chili Peppers and athletes Peyton Manning and Kobe Bryant...Dream foursome is Jack Nicklaus, Tiger Woods and his father...Biggest thrill outside golf is whitewater rafting the Arkansas River in Colorado...Twitter handle is @NateBarbee.
